{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make prescription drugs for chronic illnesses free",
        "additional_details": "HIV is a virus that requires constant medication to manage. It is unacceptable that some may be forced to miss doses due to prescription charges [1]. I myself have ADPKD-induced hypertension which means my heart rate is elevated and as such needs daily medication to lower the risk of cardiovascular disease.\r\n\r\n[1] BBC https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-40431800",
        "background": "Currently, many people pay prescription charges for chronic (lifelong) illnesses. This is essentially a lifelong tax for being unwell in some way. This is unfairly targeting those with imperfect health. The current system unfairly ranks certain illnesses above others for no apparent reason.",
